# Workspace Plan LLM Guide

## Purpose

Use this command to create a repo-local planning document for a human to fill before module implementation.

## When To Run

- Before adding a new module.
- Before changing ownership, public seams, or layer responsibilities.
- When the next coding task needs human architecture choices captured first.

## How To Read The Result

- Created means a new draft exists in `.enclosure/plans/`.
- Preserved means a draft already exists and was not overwritten.
- `--show` prints the scaffold without writing files.

## Agent Tips

- Treat plan documents as user-owned local artifacts.
- Do not overwrite an existing plan unless explicitly asked to use `--force`.
- Read a completed plan before editing application code.
